      "weather": "Fine",
      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WILD CHEVY (3) unbeaten in two runs so far and shows good promise. Hit the ground running last time and never headed, leading throughout to win by 4 lengths at this track (17.26). Two of the wins have been this track and trip. Can continue winning ways. ROCKY GALVIN (1) had been racing well with a Grade 5 win three back then placed next time before missing the frame latest at this track. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the rails draw. Well placed here and should do much better. BENTLEY ELSA (7) found trouble in the run here last time and fell. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from on outside draw. No luck latest and gets chance to atone. SACRIFICE (8) did the right thing for favourite backers last time - another big run is on the cards.",
